This paper is about Neural Architecture Search (NAS), which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a new approach to NAS that improves sample efficiency by learning the action space. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves optimization and search algorithms, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
